						<acquisition>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Giuseppe Almanzi</name> (b. 1801, d. 1860), bibliophile his manuscript no. 66; his library including 322 medieval Hebrew manuscripts were purchased en bloc by the British Museum through Asher &amp; Co. in October 1865 for £1,000 through <name type="person" role="owner">Adolphus Asher</name> (b. 1800, d. 1853), Berlin bookseller and dealer to the British Museum (see <ref target="Paisey_1997" type="page">131-153</ref>: inscribed (folio <locus n="fse001v">[81v]</locus>).</p>
							<date>1865-10</date>
						</acquisition>
